args: Comin' all the way here just to lose again?\nYe landlubbers never learn!
We'll see how much you're barking once\nyou lay eyes on our secret weapon.
Oh, aye? Go on with ye, then.
Gar, THAT be yer secret weapon?\nDon't make me be laughin'!
I've seen worse from sea cucumbers.\nYer Omega Shot is an Omega FLOP!
Now THIS, me trig lassies...\nTHIS is a shot.
Huh? Oh, what a terrible nightmare!
Thank goodness it was just a dream!
Barbary's shot knocked you unconscious.\nYou're only now waking up.
I imagine it was the harsh training along\nwith the regret of losing that did you in.\nI'm sorry we weren't more help.
Reality is reality. We lost.\nThe Omega Shot did nothing.
In that case, let us take a break and\ntry to come up with a new strategy.
Y-yes, of course... And apologies for\nmaking you all fuss over me.
Well, this is pathetic. Some captain I am!
Responsibility for a loss falls upon\nthe shoulders of the captain alone.
Patia, don't say that.\nWe lost as a team.
Pretty words that I appreciate,\nbut I still cannot forgive myself.
I...I need to be alone for a while.
No! She's still recovering!\nI'm going after her!
Patia is strong. She will be back.
I walked all day and ended up here.\nGuess the fiends don't come out at night.
Everyone believed in me.\nI was the captain and the ace.

Damn it all, I haven't been this frustrated
since I first enlisted with the Sparrows!
What was it that Captain Leif said to me
all those years ago...?
Patia, betraying trust and failing to live\nup to expectations are not synonymous.

Fortunately, you have next time.
So once you have finished your due
self-reflection, go see your fellows
who are worried about you.
He's right. I need to pull it together.

But the future we saw in the crystal ball
said we could win with the Omega Shot.
If that prediction was wrong, do we even
get another chance?
If I were to recklessly take Barbary\non and lose yet again...
If you continue to face your destiny,\nit can always be changed.
May I sit next to you, Patia?
How long have you been there, Verica?
A while now. It seems to me\nthat you are still troubled.
My Omega Shot didn't faze Barbary.\nI have no right to call myself a captain.
All of you would have been\nbetter off without me.

You may not be able to change the past,
Patia, but you can change the future.
We all must look ahead to next time
and keep doing whatever we can.
But even if we do take her on again,\nwe have no idea if we'll actually WIN.\nAnd if I were to make us lose again...
Enough of that talk. We are a team.\nWe win as one and lose that way also.
We will find a path to victory together.
But with the Omega Shot defeated...
Obtaining the Omega Shot DID make\nus stronger.
The idea of learning powerful shots\nitself may still have been a good one.\nIn which case...
Of course. We need EVERYONE'S strength!
Come on, Verica! We have to find the\nothers and have a strategy meeting!
I'll repay you for this someday, Verica!\nI swear I will!
Think nothing of it. If I was able to help\nsomeone open a path to the future,\nthat is what matters most.
Yes, thanks to all of you.\nMy apologies for worrying everyone.
You certainly seem to be in higher spirits.
Have you seen the light in some fashion?
Thanks to Verica, I'm no longer worried\nabout whether or not I'm suited to being\nthe captain of this team.
So we're going to try again!
But we used the Omega Shot and lost.\nWhat will be different next time?
Heh. We're going to have an\neven BETTER Omega Shot...
Is such a thing even possible?!
I have absolutely no idea!\nBut this is what we need to do.
We have a long road ahead of us,\nand I hope to walk it with all of you.
I know I've been a disappointment as both\nan ace and a captain, but will you beach\nvolleyball alongside me once more?
There's no win without you, Patia.
